args:
Zethia, despite supposedly being possessed by
Morsayati, awakens to find herself in a vastly
advanced civilization a thousand years in the
past. Confused as to where she is, she soon
meets Ilia, a young woman with the ability
to open otherworld gates.
Everyone foughtâ€”for themselves,\nand for those they loved.
To see one standing in the face of a great calamity,\neven though it may cost them their life...\nSuch a sight is the face of love given form.
(I am a captive, and all I can do is pray\nI am not consumed by hate.)
I grant to you a duty, prisoner.
Just so. You will bear witness to the truth,\nthen despair of it endlessly.
This is your final duty, prisoner. Now go.
I can move my body...\nBut what of the Other?
(I hear din from all around me and behold\ngreat towers of iron rising high...)
By Ilia, it is a great craft in the sky!\nSome manner of airship, perhaps?
I've seen such in books,\nbut this cannot be...
This is impossible, yet I've no choice\nbut to believe what my eyes show me.
(To my knowledge, there was only one\ntime humans boasted of an advanced\ncivilization such as this.)
(It was a thousand years ago, during the\nera in which the Goddess herself lived.)

Zethia, despite supposedly being possessed by
Morsayati, awakens to find herself in a vastly
advanced civilization a thousand years in the
past. Confused as to where she is, she soon
meets Ilia, a young woman with the ability
to open otherworld gates.
Fie, I thought I was going to be run down\nby one of those speeding iron boxes!
(I am not prepared to deal with the\nvagaries of this place yet; I must find an\narea with fewer comings and goings.)
*pant* How did I end up like this?\nWhere AM I?

(The past? Another world entirely?
No matter the case, I've not an inkling
how I could have been spirited away
to such a place.)
Lemme go! I told you, I'm not helping you!
Pray forgive the rough treatment,\nbut I fear we're simply that fervent\nabout the matter in question.
She's just some random lady I ran into.\nGot nothing to do with this.
We will be the judge of that.\n...Bring her along!
What's going on?! Who are you people?!
Okay, Augus, that's ENOUGH!\nI'm not going to let you run around\nmanhandling people like this.

This is not the way I wish to proceed
eitherâ€”but as this concerns the fate of
our great nation, one must dispense with
feelings and rely on cold fact alone.
Oh, please.\nAs if your motivations are noble!
Now then, lead the way and take us\nto your secret playground.
Then the cruel fate of this young woman\nwill be on your hands alone.
(It looks as though I've gotten myself\nembroiled in something most foul.\nOh, my brother...)
So this is the laboratory of the genius\nalchemist, eh? Ha ha ha! Remarkable!
Yay, you found it. Whoop-de-do for you.\nNow let the lady go.
Someone as bright as you must be aware\nwe didn't just come merely to observe.
Open it! Open one of your fell gates\nto the otherworld!
(Morsayati was summoned from such\na gate a thousand years ago.)
(If THIS is a thousand years in the past,\nthen it's possible that great calamity could\nbe summoned forth from this very gate!)
Stop! These gates are not something\nto be flung open so carelessly!
Hang on, random ladyâ€”how do you\neven KNOW about the gates?!
I knew you two were in cahoots!\nVery well, then...
Er, but it's not exactly ï¼‚perfectedï¼‚ yet,\nso don't go holding me responsible\nif it doesn't go how you want.
Enough distraction. I will see it done.
Okay, preparations are complete.\nHere we go...
Forcing connection of opposing poles.\nCompleted conceptual construction of\nomega key.

Dedicated mana-kiln conversion rate
steady at 80 percent. Space-time distortion
and mana phase transition detected.
Region load within allowable range.

Commencing conceptual construction of
otherworld gate... Linked.
Initiating real-number conversion from
root point to normal space.
No apparent rejection reaction to the key.\nCounting down until gate opening.\nFive...four...
Humanity would rule over all the world\nif we only could harness this power!
I TOLD you it wasn't ready!
Hey! Random lady! Can you fight?
Well, with as much mana as you have\noozing out of you, I'm guessing ï¼‚a bitï¼‚\nis gonna be more than enough.
Now let's take advantage of this chaos\nand get the heck outta here. C'mon!
(Without any concept of what was\nhappening around me, I took her hand and\nfled as fast as my legs could carry me.)
(I know only one thing: The great wheel\nof history is on the cusp of turning.)
